Eskom CEO Andre de Ruyter joins Dan Moyane on #eNCA to speak on racism allegations against him. De Ruyter has been cleared of several allegations, including racism and abuse of power. An independent inquiry has found no evidence to conclude that he is guilty of the claims. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Eskom CEO Andre de Ruyter has shared his feeling of relief after being cleared of several allegations, including racism and abuse of power. An independent inquiry found no evidence to conclude De Ruyter is guilty. READ: EXCLUSIVE: Eskom's former procurement head challenges dismissal In his report, Advocate Ishmail Semenya called the allegations by former Chief Procurement Officer Solly Tshitangano wild and highly irresponsible. Tshitangano sent copies of his allegations to several senior government officials, including President Cyril Ramaphosa and Public Enterprises Minister Pravin Gordhan. eNCA's Dan Moyane speaks to Eskom CEO Andre de Ruyter in the video above. 